Dilshan Leads Sri Lanka Comeback Against England in Second Test

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-04T18:09:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/dilshan-leads-sri-lanka-comeback-against-england-in-second-test.html
Tillakaratne Dilshan’s unbeaten
century led a  Sri Lanka  comeback against England on day two of
their second cricket Test at Lord’s in  London .  Dilshan was 127 not out as Sri Lanka reached 231-1 at
stumps to trail by 255 runs. He teamed with Tharanga
Paranavitana (65) for an opening partnership of 207. Kumar
Sangakkara will resume tomorrow on 13.  Matt Prior’s 126 led England to 486 all out in its first
innings after starting the day 342-6. Chanaka Welegedara took
four wickets and Suranga Lakmal claimed three after Sri Lanka
won the toss and elected to field.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  